The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Donald Trump at the National Prayer Breakfast on February 2, 2017. In his speech, Trump thanked faith leaders and congressional leaders for their attendance, and recognized Secretary of State Rex Tillerson. He also thanked Vice President Mike Pence for his support. Trump expressed gratitude for the prayers and faith of the American people, particularly those in the military. He emphasized the importance of freedom of religion and vowed to protect religious liberty in the country. Trump also spoke about the need for strong security measures to prevent violence and terrorism, and promised to develop a system to ensure that those entering the country embrace American values. He concluded by emphasizing the importance of faith in God and the role it plays in the success and unity of the nation.